This paper is about multi-domain neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach for domain mixing using attention modules, which involves training the model to adapt to individual domains. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper may involve image-to-text translation, which could make it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
